Pre-Game Insights: Germany manager Julian Nagelsmann is likely to hand full debuts to at least two players in Friday's UEFA Nations League clash with Bosnia-Herzegovina in Zenica.
Several key players including Kai Havertz and Jamal Musiala are injured, with Oliver Baumann expected to make his senior debut in goal.
Antonio Rudiger, Joshua Kimmich, Jonathan Tah, and Maximilian Mittelstadt are fit and will form a solid backline.
Robert Andrich and Pascal Gross are likely to form the midfield pairing, while Florian Wirtz and Serge Gnabry are expected to occupy advanced positions.
Deniz Undav is Germany's chief attacking threat, potentially joined by Jonathan Burkardt.
